The MCG email list has almost 1000 members and is an active community of discussion about museums on the web. The latest posts are shown on the right.  If you're already a list member, post to the list by sending an email to MCG@jiscmail.ac.uk.

You can join the list by going to the <a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/cgi-bin/webadmin?A0=mcg">relevant JISCmail page</a> or go straight to the <a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/cgi-bin/webadmin?SUBED1=mcg&A=1">direct link to subscribe or unsubscribe from the MCG list</a>.

The Museums Computer Group email list is a forum for discussion between museum, gallery and higher education professionals about the various uses of computing in museum contexts. We ask that you keep your posts relevant to both the computing and the cultural heritage contexts of the list, and please bear in mind that most of our members are based in the UK. <a href="http://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/help/policy/">JISCmail's Acceptable Use Policy</a> applies to this list.

If you'd rather follow the discussion in your feed reader, you can subscribe to the <a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/cgi-bin/webadmin?RSS&amp;L=MCG&amp;v=ATOM1.0">Atom</a> or <a href="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/cgi-bin/webadmin?RSS&amp;L=MCG&amp;v=2.0">RSS</a> feeds.
